Release 1.0
===========

   Release 1.0 appeared 16-Feb-1995.
   @{b}*@{ub} First public release.


@EndNode

@Node "Release 1.1" "ScreenWizard.guide/Release 1.1"
@Prev "Release 1.0"
@Toc "Revision history"

Release 1.1
===========

   Release 1.1 appeared 31-Mar-1995.

   @{b}*@{ub} Trim under screen bar can be configured in the drawing pens.

   @{b}*@{ub} Accidently used the phrase "Active window titles" twice to describe
     different pens.

   @{b}*@{ub} Double-clicking an entry now opens the attributes panel.

   @{b}*@{ub} Screen font is now configurable.

   @{b}*@{ub} Location of multicolor pens can now be configured. This should make
     things work for a combination of MUI and a MagicWB palette.

   @{b}*@{ub} Just a note: the program really is distributed as greenware, this
     is no joke.

   @{i}Important:@{ui} the format of the configuration file has changed.
ScreenWizardCX will only load config files of the newest type. However,
the prefs program can is able to load old files. I won't do this for the
commodity, because it would only make the program a bit larger. This
means that you'll have to re-save your config after installing the new
versions.


@EndNode

